Soulful singer Bukola Elemide aka Asa has said she doesn’t want to appear like a stranger in her fatherland. “I grab every opportunity to come home and perform. I do not want to be a stranger at home. Coming home this time around, I am super excited,” she said. The 39-year-old recording artist made this known while speaking ahead of her homecoming concert tagged, ‘Asa Live in Lagos.’   Nollywood suffers from lack of structure, says Dakore     StarTimes surprises Femi Adebayo with private screening of…     Omawumi, others pick six winners as Quickteller Barz and…   The live concert, in conjunction with Basketmouth, is scheduled to hold on Sunday, May 8, 2022, at the Eko Convention Centre on Victoria Island, Lagos. Speaking futther on what to expect, the Fire on the mountain singer said, “People need to see what Asa has been doing elsewhere around the world. It is a good thing to be back home performing. It is going to be a different experience. An Asa concert is one you will never forget because it is usually electric and full of life. There will be a lot of collaboration with the audience.” Asa recently released her highly anticipated sixth album entitled ‘V’ featuring Wizkid, The Cavemen, and Amaarae.